&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Product Marketing Manager, Finance owns productization and go-to-market end to end for Clearlink’s Finance vertical. The role turns recurring monetization demand into repeatable, sell-ready revenue products — anchored to revenue and gross margin — so Business Development and Partner Strategy can close faster, at higher value, and with proof that holds up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Finance centers on The Penny Hoarder and extends to any additional Clearlink brands supporting personal-finance audiences. Reporting to the SVP, Product Marketing, this role sets standard pricing and packaging for the vertical’s revenue products — Sponsorships, IAB Display, and Distribution — builds the sell-ready assets BD uses in market, keeps a continuous read on the personal-finance advertiser landscape, stays accountable for delivering what was sold, and reports on performance so every closed deal becomes proof for the next one.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Clearlink is a remote-friendly company, prioritizing virtual and in-person collaboration. This is a remote-first role for candidates who are located outside of Utah and outside of commuting distance. For candidates residing within 50 miles of our Salt Lake City, Utah office, a hybrid schedule of 2-3 days in-office is required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
